DESCRIPTION:College of the Sequoias Puente Program\, a transfer readiness
  cohort program that helps students move from community colleges to fini
 sh their bachelor’s degrees. We are planning a mini-conference for our
  local Tulare county high school students and wanted to inquire about th
 e availability of booking Las Cafeteras.
  Audience: high school and early college students primarily.\n
  Morning keynote and lunch 1 hour workshop\n
  Time: a lunch/ early afternoon activity\n
  Themes:\n
  activism\, music/creative expression and using your voice\n
  music-movement based workshop that encourages student expression and vo
 ice\n
  to get them energized and engaged in imaging their college futures.\n
  \nVENUE INFO:\n
    tel:+1 559-730-3700\n
    https://www.cos.edu/\n
  \n*************************************\nSCHEDULE:\n
  8:00 AM PDT: Load in- Ponderosa (lecture hall)\n  COLLEGE OF THE SEQUOI
 AS\n
  Parking lot 4\n
  We will get parking passes once we arrive\n
  The pass should be placed on the dashboard of your cars and it's for pa
 rking in the white stalls (yellow are reserved for faculty and staff).\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  9:00 AM PDT: Doors\n----------------------------------------\n
  9:30 AM - 10:30 AM PDT: Keynote- Know where you come from\, Know where
 you’re going\n  Play: Caravana & Presidente\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  10:30 AM - 11:30 AM PDT: Set-up & line check (bring your amps & backlin
 e)\n----------------------------------------\n
  12:30 PM - 1:30 PM PDT: Viva La Cultura/ Music sharing  -LUNCH TIME. (6
 0min)\n----------------------------------------\n
