BEGIN:VEVENT
TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:20db0925-4ba2-4fcc-8d16-d87d565f1c35
DTSTAMP:20251203T015925
SUMMARY:VOCES de la Communidad Conference- Portland
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T070000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T150000
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Perla Estrada. 503 708 6441              pestrada@
 elprograma.org
  Devon and John with Portland Productions (  portlandproductionsmgmt@g
 mail.com ) are the points of contact for all AV needs (cc'd on this ema
 il)\n
  1 hour from 1-2pm and is between conference workshops. The entire confe
 rence and band performance will remain in the same room\, so sound check
  might be tricky.\n
  VOCES de la Comunidad\, where we bring together Latine advocates and al
 lys from across Oregon and Washington to learn\, share\, and be in commu
 nity in support of each other and the Latine survivors they serve everyd
 ay. The entire conference is presented in Spanish (non-spanish speakers
 are provided with interpretation services) and rooted in the healing pow
 er of our cultura.\n
  The UNICA program\, which provides services to survivors of domestic\,
 sexual\, and trafficking violence serves between 300-350 survivors and t
 heir families annually. UNICA is the first and only\, fully bilingual Cr
 isis Line for survivors in the state of Oregon. Our advocates answer tha
 t line 24/7 to provide emotional support\, safety planning\, information
  and referral\, emergency hotel vouchers and/or transportation for anyon
 e fleeing iminent violence. Our case management advocates can provide in
 tensive wrap around support for survivors and their families\, from fili
 ng reports all the way through support with long term housing.\n
  \nVENUE INFO:\n
    tel:+1 503-281-6111\n
    https://www.hilton.com/en/hotels/rllc-dt-doubletree-portland/?SEO_id=
 GMB-AMER-DT-RLLCDT&y_source=1_MTM3MjY5Mi03MTUtbG9jYXRpb24ud2Vic2l0ZQ%3D%
 3D\n
  \n*************************************\nSCHEDULE:\n
  7:15 AM PDT: Lobby (get breakfast at cafe in lobby)/load\n-------------
 ---------------------------\n
  7:45 AM - 11:00 AM PDT: Drive out\n------------------------------------
 ----\n
  9:00 AM PDT: Conference starts\n---------------------------------------
 -\n
  11:15 AM - 12:00 PM PDT: Load/set up\n---------------------------------
 -------\n
  12:00 PM - 12:30 PM PDT: Personal prep in green room\n-----------------
 -----------------------\n
  12:30 PM - 1:00 PM PDT: Line check (lunch starts)\n--------------------
 --------------------\n
  1:15 PM - 2:15 PM PDT: Showtime (1 hr)\n-------------------------------
 ---------\n
